         <h3>Why Are Donkey's not allow to sleep in Bathtubs in Arizona?</h3>
        <div class='col-lg-6'>
            <img class='img-responsive' src='img/donkey.jpg' width='400px'>
        </div>
        <p>Arizona, oh Arizona. We know states have crazy laws, but this one is particularly crazy. It turns out that it is illegal in the state for a Donkey to sleep in a Bathtub. The big question is why?</p>
        <p>According to answers.yahoo.com, this is the best explanation: It's based on a 1924 case where a merchant's donkey started sleeping in an old bathtub that was supposed to be filled with his drinking water. When the local damn broke
            a flood ensued and the donkey was washed away in the tub. The tub and donkey survived the trip down the valley for a mile until the water receded. The law was passed because several of the townspeople signed a petition against
            such a thing after they had to wrangle the donkey and haul the merchant's *** back to his house.</p>
        <p>So remember kids, when in Arizona, and you have a Donkey in your house (or any type of home), please remember: Keep them out of your bathtub or you'll be BREAKING THE LAW!</p>
